---
title: Tangy Ginger Steak & Pepper Stir-Fry with Carrot & Scallion Rice
description: Our chefs whipped up a dreamy sauce of plum jam, rich stock, ponzu sauce, fresh lemon juice, and a swirl of butter to add sweet, tangy, and aromatic complexity to tender, gingery, garlicky steak stir-fry. Serve alongside colorful sautéed bell peppers and carrots atop buttery scallion rice. What else can we say—it’s plum tasty!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67d7de4b6526e41d967ae65c-20df8c2b.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67d7de4b6526e41d967ae65c-en-US.pdf
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 95 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 930 mg
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tangy-ginger-steak-and-pepper-stir-fry-67d7de4b6526e41d967ae65c
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{3%oz} on a diagonal into 1/4-inch-thick pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Pat @ranch steak{10%oz} dry with paper towels and thinly slice against the grain.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine steak, garlic, @ginger paste{1%oz}, @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Toss until thoroughly coated. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and carrot and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Don't worry if the steak sticks a bit; it will release from the pan once it's cooked.

While steak cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @plum jam{1%unit}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, 1/4 cup water, and juice from one lemon wedge (1/3 cup water and juice from two wedges for 4 servings).

Add sauce to pan with steak and cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Stir in veggies; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in scallion greens and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with stir-fry. Serve.

> Be fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.